# Custom IDE with Ollama Integration - MOSS Architecture
# Version: 2.0-dual_system
# Date: 2026-04-22
# Purpose: Define VS Code-like IDE with shared Ollama, dual-pane editor (Windows + Ubuntu Worker 1 remote view), and script execution

[SYSTEM]
Name: CustomIDE_DualPane_SharedOllama
Description: Windows IDE (VS Code-like) with dual panes: local editor + remote Ubuntu Worker 1 IDE view. Shared Ollama version across both systems for model consistency. Capable of reading, applying, and executing scripts locally and on Worker 1.
Owner: AI_Assistant
Status: architecture_draft
Key_Constraint: OLLAMA_VERSION must be identical on Windows and Ubuntu Worker 1

---

# RESOURCES - System Components

[R:Ollama_Version_Coordinator]
Type: Configuration/Service
Location: Windows: localhost:11434 | Ubuntu: localhost:11434 (same version deployed to both)
Description: Centrally specified Ollama version ensuring model consistency across Windows IDE and Ubuntu Worker 1
Responsibilities:
  - Define canonical Ollama version (e.g., "ollama:latest" or pinned version)
  - Provide version specification file readable by both systems
  - Enable model syncing (same mistral/neural-chat/etc on both)
Canonical_Version_File: c:\AI Assistant\MIDE\pilot_v1\config\ollama_version.txt (and mirrored on Worker 1)
Models_Pinned:
  - model_primary: "mistral:7b" (or user choice)
  - model_backup: "neural-chat:7b"
Quality: Version mismatch between Windows and Ubuntu would cause inconsistent code generation → must be enforced
Accessed_By: IDE_Backend_Windows, IDE_Backend_Ubuntu (via MIDE worker)

---

[R:IDE_Frontend_Windows]
Type: Application/UI
Location: c:\AI Assistant\customide\frontend
Language: HTML/JavaScript (Electron or web-based)
Description: VS Code-like IDE interface running on Windows desktop with dual-pane design and full code editor capabilities
Architecture:
  Pane_Left:
    - Primary code editor (ace/monaco-like)
    - File tabs (open multiple files)
    - Syntax highlighting (Python, JavaScript, Bash, JSON, etc.)
    - Line numbers + gutter markers
    - Search/replace (Ctrl+H)
    - File explorer (project tree)
    - Git status indicators
  Pane_Right:
    - Remote view of Ubuntu Worker 1 IDE (via SSH terminal or iframe-like remote display)
    - Allows monitoring/interaction with remote environment
    - Shows remote file system, terminal output
  Global_UI:
    - Sidebar: File Explorer, Search, Git, Extensions-like panel
    - Top Bar: File menu, Edit, View, Run, Help
    - Bottom Status Bar: Line/Col, Git branch, Ollama connection status, Worker 1 status
    - Integrated Terminal (Ctrl+`)
    - Command Palette (Ctrl+Shift+P)
Responsibilities:
  - Display code with syntax highlighting
  - Tab management (open/close files)
  - Split-pane view management
  - Accept Ollama AI requests (Ctrl+Space completion, Ctrl+Alt+G for generation)
  - Display script execution results
  - Show remote Ubuntu IDE in right pane
Dependencies: IDE_Backend_Windows, SSH_Worker1_Bridge, Remote_IDE_View
Exposes:
  - GET /health
  - GET /files/{path}
  - GET /file/{path}
  - POST /editor/open (tab management)
  - POST /editor/save
  - POST /ollama/complete
  - POST /ollama/generate
  - POST /script/apply
  - POST /script/execute
  - POST /remote/connect (SSH to Worker 1)

---

[R:IDE_Backend_Windows]
Type: Server/Coordinator
Location: c:\AI Assistant\customide\backend
Language: Python (FastAPI)
Description: Local server coordinating IDE operations, bridges UI to Ollama, script execution, and Worker 1
Responsibilities:
  - Expose REST API for IDE_Frontend_Windows
  - Accept code + context for AI requests
  - Forward to Ollama_Version_Coordinator (localhost:11434)
  - Handle script reading, validation, and execution
  - Coordinate SSH connections to Worker 1
  - Manage file system I/O
  - Route remote IDE display requests to Worker 1
Port: 5555
Dependencies: Ollama_Version_Coordinator, Script_Execution_Engine, SSH_Worker1_Bridge, File_System_Local, Git_Integration
Consumes:
  - Editor state + AI requests from IDE_Frontend_Windows
  - Code generation from Ollama_Version_Coordinator
  - Script output from Script_Execution_Engine
  - Remote data from SSH_Worker1_Bridge
Produces:
  - Formatted suggestions to IDE_Frontend_Windows
  - Script execution results
  - Remote view data for right pane

---

[R:SSH_Worker1_Bridge]
Type: Communication/Tunnel
Location: Connects Windows IDE_Backend to Ubuntu Worker 1 (~ubuntu-worker-01)
Description: SSH tunnel for secure command execution and file access on remote Ubuntu system
Responsibilities:
  - Establish SSH session to Worker 1
  - Execute scripts remotely (bash, python)
  - Query remote filesystem
  - Retrieve remote IDE state
  - Forward Ollama requests to remote Ollama instance (consistency check)
SSH_Config:
  - Host: ubuntu-atlas-01 (FQDN or IP)
  - Port: 22
  - User: larieladmin
  - Auth: SSH key (stored securely)
  - Persist_Session: true (keep tunnel alive)
Dependencies: Worker_1_Ubuntu_System
Exposes:
  - exec_remote_script(script_path, args) → output
  - query_remote_fs(path) → file tree
  - get_remote_ide_state() → current file, line, terminal state

---

[R:Remote_IDE_View]
Type: Display/Window
Location: Right pane of IDE_Frontend_Windows
Description: Live view of Ubuntu Worker 1's IDE and terminal environment
Responsibilities:
  - Display remote filesystem browser (read-only or editable)
  - Show active remote terminal session
  - Display Worker 1's recent script outputs
  - Show active task/mtask status
  - Allow user to switch focus between local and remote
Data_Source: SSH_Worker1_Bridge queries
Refresh_Rate: 1 second (or on-demand)
Quality: Must not block local IDE responsiveness; async updates

---

[R:Script_Execution_Engine]
Type: Runtime/Executor
Location: Embedded in IDE_Backend_Windows
Description: Reads, validates, and executes scripts (Bash, Python, PowerShell) locally and on Worker 1
Responsibilities:
  - Read script from file system
  - Parse script headers for metadata (dependencies, runtime requirements)
  - Validate syntax before execution
  - Execute locally OR forward to Worker 1 via SSH_Worker1_Bridge
  - Capture stdout/stderr/exit_code
  - Display results in IDE terminal
  - Support script arguments and environment variables
Supported_Runtimes:
  - Python (python3)
  - Bash (bash)
  - PowerShell (pwsh)
  - Node.js (node) - optional
Safety_Constraints:
  - Require user confirmation for script execution
  - No execution of scripts from untrusted sources
  - Timeout protection (default 60s, user-adjustable)
Dependencies: File_System_Local, SSH_Worker1_Bridge
Exposes:
  - execute_local(script_path, args, timeout)
  - execute_remote(script_path, args, host, timeout)
  - validate_script(script_path)

---

[R:Ollama_Local_Server]
Type: External AI Service
Location: localhost:11434 (Windows) + localhost:11434 (Ubuntu Worker 1)
Description: Ollama instance for code generation, completion, refactoring - SAME VERSION on both systems
Responsibilities:
  - Accept code prompts from IDE_Backend_Windows
  - Generate/complete/refactor code using models specified by Ollama_Version_Coordinator
  - Stream or batch responses
Version: Must match Ollama_Version_Coordinator spec (enforced at deployment)
Models_Required:
  - Primary: mistral:7b (or pinned version)
  - Backup: neural-chat:7b
Exposes:
  - POST /api/generate (streaming text generation)
  - POST /api/chat (chat-based requests)
  - GET /api/tags (list available models)
Dependencies: None (external, pre-existing)
Quality_Notes: Both Windows and Ubuntu instances must be version-identical to ensure reproducible code generation

---

[R:File_System_Local]
Type: Storage/Filesystem
Location: c:\AI Assistant\customide\projects\{project_name}
Description: Local Windows filesystem for project code files
Responsibilities:
  - Store source code, configs, docs, scripts
  - Support read/write operations from IDE_Backend_Windows
  - Track file metadata (modification time, size, type)
  - Support .gitignore filtering
Dependencies: IDE_Backend_Windows, Script_Execution_Engine
Accessed_By: IDE_Backend_Windows, IDE_Frontend_Windows

---

[R:Git_Integration]
Type: Version Control
Location: c:\AI Assistant\customide\projects\{project_name}\.git
Description: Git repository for version control and remote sync
Responsibilities:
  - Manage local commits
  - Track file changes (staged/unstaged)
  - Support push/pull to remote (e.g., GitHub)
  - Provide status queries
Dependencies: File_System_Local, IDE_Backend_Windows
Accessed_By: IDE_Backend_Windows, IDE_Frontend_Windows

---

[R:Worker_1_Ubuntu_System]
Type: External System
Location: ubuntu-worker-01 / ubuntu-atlas-01 (ngrok accessible)
Description: Ubuntu server with MIDE autopilot, Worker 1 IDE, and remote Ollama instance
Responsibilities:
  - Run autonomous mtask jobs
  - Execute scripts via SSH from Windows IDE
  - Provide IDE interface (VSCode server or similar on Ubuntu)
  - Run Ollama instance (VERSION-COORDINATED with Windows)
  - Support remote file access via SSH
Status: Operational (from weather demo)
SSH_Access: Enabled via SSH_Worker1_Bridge
IDE_on_Remote: Must expose IDE interface for right-pane viewing
Ollama_Instance: Must match Windows version exactly

---

# ACTIONS - Data Flows & Operations

[ACT:Script_Read_Validate_Apply]
Trigger: User selects a script file (.sh, .py, .ps1) in file explorer, right-clicks "Read and Apply"
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows requests script content via GET /file/{script_path}
  2. IDE_Backend_Windows reads from File_System_Local
  3. Script_Execution_Engine validates syntax (python -m py_compile, bash -n, etc.)
  4. IDE_Frontend displays script content in editor panel + metadata (runtime required, args)
  5. User reviews script and clicks "Apply"
  6. On Apply: IDE_Backend_Windows shows diff/preview before execution
  7. User confirms execution
Response_Time: <1 second for read/validate, execution time depends on script

---

[ACT:Script_Execute_Local]
Trigger: User clicks "Execute" button in script panel (or Ctrl+Shift+E in script file)
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows sends POST /script/execute with:
     - script_path
     - arguments (if parameterized)
     - timeout (default 60s)
     - capture_output: true
  2. IDE_Backend_Windows routes to Script_Execution_Engine
  3. Script_Execution_Engine executes locally:
     - Spawns subprocess (python3, bash, pwsh)
     - Captures stdout, stderr, exit_code
     - Enforces timeout
  4. IDE_Backend_Windows collects results
  5. IDE_Frontend displays output in integrated terminal + status (success/failure)
  6. User can re-execute or modify parameters
Response_Time: Script execution time + 100ms overhead

---

[ACT:Script_Execute_Remote_Worker1]
Trigger: User selects "Execute on Worker 1" (right-click in script, or button toggle)
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows sends POST /script/execute-remote with:
     - script_path
     - arguments
     - target_host: "ubuntu-worker-01"
     - timeout
  2. IDE_Backend_Windows routes to SSH_Worker1_Bridge
  3. SSH_Worker1_Bridge establishes SSH session (if not persistent)
  4. SSH_Worker1_Bridge validates script exists on remote
  5. SSH_Worker1_Bridge executes: ssh user@host "bash /path/to/script.sh {args}"
  6. Captures remote stdout/stderr/exit_code
  7. IDE_Backend_Windows buffers results
  8. IDE_Frontend displays in terminal + updates Remote_IDE_View with output
  9. User can execute again or view logs on Worker 1
Response_Time: SSH latency (50-200ms) + script execution time

---

[ACT:Ollama_Version_Sync_Check]
Trigger: IDE starts up OR user clicks "Verify Ollama Consistency"
Flow:
  1. IDE_Backend_Windows reads Ollama_Version_Coordinator spec (c:\AI Assistant\...\ollama_version.txt)
  2. IDE_Backend queries localhost:11434/api/tags to get installed version
  3. IDE_Backend queries Worker 1 via SSH: "ollama --version" + list models
  4. Compares versions
  5. If mismatch:
     - Display warning in status bar (🔴 Ollama version mismatch)
     - Suggest: pull latest on Worker 1 via mtask
     - Disable code generation until synced
  6. If match:
     - Display ✅ in status bar
     - Ready for AI requests
Response_Time: <2 seconds

---

[ACT:Dual_Pane_Switch]
Trigger: User clicks right-pane "Connect to Worker 1" button or presses Alt+Right
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows requests POST /remote/connect
  2. IDE_Backend_Windows calls SSH_Worker1_Bridge.establish_session()
  3. SSH_Worker1_Bridge queries Worker 1:
     - "whoami" (verify connection)
     - "pwd" (current directory)
     - "ls -la" (file tree)
     - PS output (if IDE running on Worker 1)
  4. Remote_IDE_View receives data
  5. IDE_Frontend right pane displays:
     - Remote file browser
     - Active terminal session output
     - Recent mtask status
  6. User can interact: click files, run commands, view logs
Response_Time: SSH round-trip (100-200ms) + UI render

---

[ACT:Terminal_Execution_Integrated]
Trigger: User types command in IDE integrated terminal (Ctrl+`)
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows captures command input
  2. IDE_Backend_Windows routes to Script_Execution_Engine (or direct shell)
  3. Script_Execution_Engine executes in subprocess
  4. Output streams back to IDE terminal in real-time
  5. User can chain commands, use pipes, environment variables
Response_Time: <100ms per line

---

[ACT:Code_Completion_Request]
Trigger: User types in IDE editor or presses hotkey (Ctrl+Space)
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows captures editor context (current file + surrounding lines)
  2. IDE_Frontend sends POST /ollama/complete to IDE_Backend_Windows with:
     - file_path
     - current_line_number
     - cursor_position
     - file_contents (full or excerpt)
     - language (python, javascript, bash, etc.)
  3. IDE_Backend_Windows formats prompt for Ollama_Version_Coordinator (localhost:11434)
  4. Ollama_Local_Server (Windows instance) generates completion suggestions (streaming)
  5. IDE_Backend_Windows buffers and formats response
  6. IDE_Frontend receives JSON with suggestions
  7. IDE_Frontend displays in autocomplete dropdown or inline
Response_Time: 1-5 seconds (dependent on Ollama hardware)

---

[ACT:Code_Generation_Request]
Trigger: User writes natural language comment or prompt in editor
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows captures user prompt + file context
  2. IDE_Frontend sends POST /ollama/generate to IDE_Backend_Windows with:
     - prompt (user's natural language)
     - file_path
     - context_lines (code before/after insertion point)
     - language
  3. IDE_Backend_Windows sends detailed prompt to Ollama_Version_Coordinator (localhost:11434)
  4. Ollama_Local_Server (Windows) generates code (streaming)
  5. IDE_Backend_Windows accumulates response
  6. IDE_Frontend displays in modal/panel with approve/reject buttons
  7. On approve: code inserted into editor
  8. On reject: discarded
Response_Time: 3-10 seconds

---

[ACT:Code_Refactoring_Request]
Trigger: User selects code block + menu action "Refactor with Ollama"
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows captures selected text + language
  2. IDE_Frontend sends POST /ollama/refactor to IDE_Backend_Windows with:
     - selected_code
     - language
     - refactoring_goal (simplify, optimize, add_types, etc.)
  3. IDE_Backend_Windows crafts refactoring prompt
  4. Ollama_Version_Coordinator generates refactored code
  5. IDE_Frontend shows diff view (original vs refactored)
  6. On approve: replaces selection
  7. On reject: no change

---

[ACT:File_Save_and_Git_Commit]
Trigger: User saves file (Ctrl+S) + manually commits in Git panel
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows detects file save
  2. File_System_Local writes changes
  3. IDE_Backend_Windows queries Git_Integration for modified files
  4. Git status shown in IDE left panel (untracked, modified, staged)
  5. User clicks "Stage" → IDE_Backend_Windows runs git add {file}
  6. User writes commit message + clicks "Commit"
  7. IDE_Backend_Windows runs git commit -m "{message}"
  8. IDE_Frontend updates status display
  9. Optional: User clicks "Push" → git push to remote
Response_Time: <1 second per operation

---

[ACT:Project_Open]
Trigger: User clicks "Open Project" or starts IDE
Flow:
  1. IDE_Frontend_Windows shows project browser or accepts folder path
  2. IDE_Backend_Windows scans folder for .git, project structure
  3. IDE_Backend_Windows reads Git_Integration status
  4. IDE_Backend_Windows reads File_System_Local directory tree
  5. IDE_Frontend displays file tree, git status summary, left pane ready for code editing
  6. Right pane (Remote_IDE_View) prompts to "Connect to Worker 1"
  7. Ready for code editing + remote monitoring

---

# INTERFACES - Communication Contracts

[INT:IDEBackend_OllamaVersion_REST]
Protocol: HTTP/REST (streaming JSON)
Port: IDE_Backend_Windows calls localhost:11434 (Windows Ollama)
Consistency: Must verify Windows Ollama version matches Worker_1_Ubuntu_System Ollama version
Request_Format (to Ollama):
  {
    "model": "mistral:7b",  // Pinned from Ollama_Version_Coordinator
    "prompt": "{formatted_prompt}",
    "stream": true,
    "temperature": 0.7,
    "context": [...]
  }
Response_Format (from Ollama):
  Line 1: {"response": "chunk1", "done": false}
  Line 2: {"response": "chunk2", "done": false}
  Line N: {"response": "", "done": true}
Latency_Target: <5s for completion, <10s for generation
Version_Check: On IDE startup + periodically verify against Worker 1

---

[INT:IDEFrontend_IDEBackend_HTTP]
Protocol: HTTP/REST (JSON)
Port: 5555
Base_URL: http://127.0.0.1:5555

Endpoint: GET /health
Response:
  {
    "status": "ok",
    "ollama_version": "0.x.x",
    "ollama_sync": "matched",  // or "mismatch_warning"
    "worker_connected": true
  }

Endpoint: POST /ollama/complete
Request:
  {
    "file_path": "src/main.py",
    "line_number": 42,
    "cursor_pos": 15,
    "file_contents": "import os\n...",
    "language": "python"
  }
Response:
  {
    "suggestions": [
      {"text": "os.listdir()", "score": 0.95},
      {"text": "os.path.exists()", "score": 0.85}
    ],
    "latency_ms": 2340
  }

Endpoint: POST /ollama/generate
Request:
  {
    "prompt": "write a function to validate email",
    "file_path": "src/validators.py",
    "language": "python",
    "context_lines": 5
  }
Response:
  {
    "generated_code": "def validate_email(email: str) -> bool:\n    import re\n    return re.match(...)",
    "model_used": "mistral:7b",
    "latency_ms": 6500
  }

Endpoint: POST /script/validate
Request:
  {
    "script_path": "scripts/deploy.sh",
    "language": "bash"
  }
Response:
  {
    "valid": true,
    "syntax_check": "passed",
    "runtime_required": "bash",
    "args": []
  }

Endpoint: POST /script/execute
Request:
  {
    "script_path": "scripts/test.py",
    "arguments": ["--verbose"],
    "timeout": 60,
    "capture_output": true,
    "target": "local"  // or "worker1"
  }
Response:
  {
    "success": true,
    "exit_code": 0,
    "stdout": "Test results...",
    "stderr": "",
    "execution_time_ms": 1234
  }

Endpoint: POST /script/execute-remote
Request:
  {
    "script_path": "scripts/deploy.sh",
    "arguments": ["production"],
    "target_host": "ubuntu-worker-01",
    "timeout": 120
  }
Response:
  {
    "success": true,
    "exit_code": 0,
    "stdout": "Deployment complete",
    "stderr": "",
    "remote_host": "ubuntu-worker-01",
    "execution_time_ms": 45000
  }

Endpoint: POST /git/status
Response:
  {
    "branch": "main",
    "modified": ["src/main.py", "README.md"],
    "untracked": ["test_output.log"],
    "staged": [],
    "ahead": 0,
    "behind": 0
  }

Endpoint: POST /git/commit
Request:
  {
    "message": "feat: add email validation",
    "files": ["src/validators.py"]
  }
Response:
  {
    "success": true,
    "commit_hash": "a1b2c3d",
    "message": "feat: add email validation"
  }

Endpoint: POST /remote/connect
Request:
  {
    "host": "ubuntu-atlas-01",
    "port": 22
  }
Response:
  {
    "connected": true,
    "current_dir": "/home/larieladmin/projects",
    "user": "larieladmin",
    "shell": "/bin/bash"
  }

Endpoint: GET /remote/files
Response:
  {
    "path": "/home/larieladmin/projects",
    "files": [
      {"name": "project1", "type": "dir", "modified": "2026-04-22T12:00:00Z"},
      {"name": "script.sh", "type": "file", "size": 2048}
    ]
  }

Endpoint: GET /remote/terminal
Response (streaming):
  Last 100 lines of remote terminal output for display in right pane

---

[INT:IDEBackend_SSHWorker1_Tunnel]
Protocol: SSH/Command Execution
Port: 22 (standard SSH)
Target: ubuntu-worker-01 / ubuntu-atlas-01
Auth: SSH key (stored securely in IDE config)
Commands_Executed:
  - ssh user@host "python3 /path/to/script.py {args}"
  - ssh user@host "bash -n /path/to/script.sh" (syntax check)
  - ssh user@host "ollama --version" (version check)
  - ssh user@host "ls -la /remote/path" (file browsing)
  - ssh user@host "cd /path && pwd" (navigation)
Persistence: SSH connection pooling (keep-alive)
Quality: Latency ~100-200ms per round-trip

