# ABSTRACTIONS - System Dependencies & Architecture

[ABS:IDE_System_Layers]
Layer 1 (Presentation): IDE_Frontend_Windows (dual-pane UI)
  - Left pane: Local code editor (VS Code-like)
  - Right pane: Remote Ubuntu IDE view
  - User interactions
  - File tabs, explorer, status bar
Layer 2 (Coordination): IDE_Backend_Windows
  - Request routing (AI, script, git, remote)
  - Context management
  - Response formatting
  - SSH tunnel management to Worker 1
Layer 3 (Intelligence): Ollama_Version_Coordinator (Windows + Ubuntu)
  - Code generation (AI reasoning)
  - Model consistency enforcement
Layer 4 (Execution): Script_Execution_Engine
  - Local script execution
  - Remote execution via SSH_Worker1_Bridge
Layer 5 (Persistence): File_System_Local + Git_Integration
  - Local data storage
  - Version control
  - Remote filesystem access via SSH

[ABS:Dual_Pane_Architecture]
Left_Pane: IDE_Frontend_Windows local editor
  - Active development
  - Local file navigation
  - Local script execution with visible output
  - Git operations (commit, status, push)
  
Right_Pane: Remote_IDE_View (Ubuntu Worker 1)
  - Read-only or limited-edit remote filesystem
  - Remote terminal session
  - mtask execution status
  - Remote script outputs
  - Live synchronization via SSH_Worker1_Bridge

[ABS:Data_Flow_Architecture]
Synchronous_Flows (user waits for response):
  - Code completion → Ollama_Version_Coordinator (Windows) → IDE display (<3s)
  - Code generation → Ollama_Version_Coordinator → IDE display (<10s)
  - Git status query → filesystem → IDE display (<1s)
  - Script validation → Script_Execution_Engine → IDE display (<1s)
  - Remote file list → SSH_Worker1_Bridge → right pane (<200ms)

Asynchronous_Flows (background operations):
  - File watcher triggers on save
  - Ollama version sync check (Worker 1 vs Windows)
  - Remote IDE state refresh (1s poll)
  - Background script execution on Worker 1

[ABS:Ollama_Version_Coordination]
Constraint: Windows and Ubuntu Worker 1 MUST use identical Ollama versions
Enforcement:
  - Canonical version spec in c:\AI Assistant\MIDE\pilot_v1\config\ollama_version.txt
  - On IDE startup: compare localhost:11434 version with remote (via SSH)
  - On version mismatch: warn user + disable code generation
  - Admin can trigger MTASK to update Worker 1 Ollama via IDE UI

[ABS:Script_Execution_Capability]
Local_Execution: IDE_Backend_Windows → Script_Execution_Engine → local subprocess
Remote_Execution: IDE_Backend_Windows → SSH_Worker1_Bridge → Worker_1_Ubuntu_System

Read_Apply_Flow:
  1. User selects script in file explorer
  2. IDE_Backend reads + displays in editor
  3. User reviews content + metadata
  4. User clicks "Execute" → Choose local or remote
  5. Script_Execution_Engine validates syntax
  6. On approve: execute with user confirmation
  7. Output streamed to integrated terminal

[ABS:Integration_with_MIDE_Worker]
Assumption: Custom IDE and MIDE autopilot are complementary
- MIDE handles: autonomous task execution, mtask jobs, scheduled operations
- Custom IDE handles: interactive development, testing, debugging, script management
- SSH_Worker1_Bridge enables IDE to trigger scripts on Worker 1
- Shared filesystem: both can read/write MIDE repo
- Shared Ollama: consistent code generation across both systems

---

# QUALITY & NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

[QFR:Performance]
- Code completion: <3 seconds
- Code generation: <10 seconds
- Script validation: <1 second
- Local script execution: depends on script (timeout 60s default)
- Remote script execution: SSH latency (100-200ms) + script time
- Git operations: <1 second
- File browser (local): instant (<100ms)
- Remote file browser: <200ms (SSH query)
- Ollama version check: <2 seconds
- Tab switching: instant

[QFR:Availability]
- IDE requires local Ollama running (mismatched version shows warning, disables AI)
- SSH to Worker 1 optional (IDE works without it, just local mode)
- Fallback: disable AI features if Ollama unavailable
- Git can work offline; push/pull requires network
- Script execution can target local OR remote independently

[QFR:Usability]
- Dual-pane layout (VS Code-inspired)
- Dark theme (consistent with weather GUI)
- Keyboard shortcuts: Ctrl+Space (complete), Ctrl+/ (comment), Ctrl+Shift+P (palette), Ctrl+` (terminal)
- Split-pane draggable divider
- Status bar: current file, line/col, git branch, Ollama version status, Worker 1 connection status
- File tabs with unsaved indicator (•)
- Syntax highlighting: Python, JavaScript, Bash, JSON, YAML, Markdown
- Integrated terminal (bottom of left pane)

[QFR:Security]
- Local Ollama: no auth required (localhost only)
- SSH to Worker 1: key-based auth (no passwords)
- Git credentials: use system keychain or .git/config
- No secrets in code (enforce .gitignore)
- Script execution: require user confirmation before running
- Script timeout protection: max 300s configurable
- SSH connection: pooled, keep-alive, auto-reconnect on disconnect

[QFR:Scalability]
- Support projects up to 10MB local (file indexing)
- Remote filesystem browsing via SSH (on-demand lazy loading)
- Streaming responses from Ollama (no memory bloat)
- Connection pooling to Worker 1 (persistent SSH session)
- Tab limit: reasonable (recommend <50 open files)

